ry=ttu','3102 Lake Farm Rd, Madison, WI 53711',0,1,NULL,NULL),(33,'Chippewa Moraine State Recreation Area','Chippewa','Interprets varied glacial landforms. The park is a unit of the Ice Age National Scientific Reserve.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Chippewa+Moraine+State+Recreation+Area/@45.2227353,-91.4159912,16.43z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x52aca3c111014ba5:0x5ceb55a59a8ba577!8m2!3d45.2235158!4d-91.4140998!16zL20vMGgzdGho?entry=ttu','13394 Co Hwy M, New Auburn, WI 54757',0,1,NULL,NULL),(34,'Copper Culture State Park','Oconto','Interprets a burial ground used by the Old Copper Culture from 3000 to 2000 BCE. The site is a National Historic Landmark','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Copper+Culture+State+Park/@44.8858786,-87.9058916,15.28z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x88029921e282b7c7:0x749833e42becfdc!8m2!3d44.8878308!4d-87.8978126!16s%2Fm%2F0260tbn?entry=ttu','260 Copper Culture Way, Oconto, WI 54153',0,0,NULL,NULL),(35,'Copper Falls State Park','Ashland','Contains 7.5 miles (12.1 km) of the Bad River, including a 2-mile (3.2 km) gorge with several waterfalls. The park is listed on the NRHP.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Copper+Falls+State+Park/@46.3727867,-90.6476557,15.1z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x52a97844c03cc3d3:0xfd1bede6c98d82!8m2!3d46.3761555!4d-90.6439684!16s%2Fm%2F04cs4p7?entry=ttu','36764 Copper Falls Rd, Mellen, WI 54546',1,1,NULL,NULL),(36,'Council Grounds State Park','Lincoln','Lies on a riverbank where Native Americans were said to have once held councils.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Council+Grounds+State+Park/@45.1854287,-89.7425256,14.98z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x4d554653979be359:0x3b057b09c65beccc!8m2!3d45.187002!4d-89.7345548!16s%2Fm%2F04cr12w?entry=ttu','N1895 Council Grounds Dr, Merrill, WI 54452',1,1,NULL,NULL),(37,'Cross Plains State Park','Dane','A unit of the Ice Age National Scientific Reserve. Consists of land owned by Dane County, the Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources, the National Park Service, and the United States Fish and Wildlife Service.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Cross+Plains+State+Park/@43.082261,-89.6117868,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x8807a3afd56cd55f:0xf77537391c11e99f!8m2!3d43.082261!4d-89.6092119!16s%2Fg%2F11gy8gjyl7?entry=ttu','Cross Plains, WI 53528',0,1,NULL,NULL),(38,'Devil\'s Lake State Park','Sauk','Protects a 360-acre (150 ha) endorheic lake in the Baraboo Range, hemmed in by moraines and 500-foot (150 m) quartzite bluffs.The park is a unit of the Ice Age National Scientific Reserve.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Devil\'s+Lake+State+Park/@43.4284471,-89.7339427,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x88076b09e9bb0cc5:0xc3dff582d677d7c3!8m2!3d43.4284471!4d-89.7313678!16zL20vMDZjcTdm?entry=ttu','S5975 Park Rd, Baraboo, WI 53913',1,1,NULL,NULL),(39,'Fischer Creek State Recreation Area','Manitowoc','Preserves a mile of shoreline flanking the mouth of Fischer Creek. Managed by the Manitowoc County Park System.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Fischer+Creek+Park/@43.9330565,-87.7276582,15.25z/data=!4m14!1m7!3m6!1s0x8803453c2c966b43:0x95bf076535692aa6!2sFischer+Creek!8m2!3d43.9358067!4d-87.7678495!16s%2Fm%2F04cs392!3m5!1s0x8803452917a750a9:0xe3f038f30a5053b4!8m2!3d43.93994!4d-87.72092!16s%2Fg%2F11p0gl5jn4?entry=ttu','13281 Lakeshore Rd, Cleveland, WI 53015',0,0,NULL,NULL),(40,'Governor Dodge State Park','Iowa','Preserves Driftless Area topography in memory of Henry Dodge, settler and first governor of the Wisconsin Territory.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Governor+Dodge+State+Park/@43.0248429,-90.1123285,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m6!3m5!1s0x87fd7b292a51c4cb:0x39518e7d7871721b!8m2!3d43.024843!4d-90.1074576!16zL20vMDl3NXA4?entry=ttu','4175 WI-23, Dodgeville, WI 53533',1,1,NULL,NULL),(41,'Governor Nelson State Park','Dane','Contains a 500-foot (150 m) beach, restored prairie, and ancient Indian mounds.','https://www.google.com/maps/place/Governor+Nelson+State+Park/@43.1351888,-89.4410534,16.31z/data=!4m6!3m5!1s0x8807aafe2cb19e69:0x6830795a23efc352!8m2!3d43.1375035!4d-89.4399226!16zL20vM